			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p129587"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Gigienc</strong> &raquo; Wed Dec 27, 2006 11:22 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Something important to mention concerning stopping and casting.
<br />
<br />When you move, the game engine updates your position at intervals. When you make a turn from a straight line, it forces an update immediately.
<br />
<br />When you stop, hit the turn key just a tap, then start casting. This &quot;twitch&quot; cuts down on interrupts almost totally.</div>

