			<h3 ><a href="#p138817">Re: HoH Solo Charming Questions</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Dally</strong> &raquo; Wed Mar 12, 2008 6:48 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">If you want to kill 10 or more Mobs with One pet here's the 'secret' ( no big secret )<br /><br /><br />Haste your Pet, with the Highest Haste.<br />Most people don't think of this, but 'Scarecrow' Your Pet. Not only saves him some health, but makes charm breaks less confusing... Which ones your former pet? Hmm.. could be the one with a Pumpkin Head.<br />Cast Strengthen on your pet.<br />Cast Feedback ( dmg shield ) on your pet.<br /><br />Slow the MOB.<br />Cripple the Mob.<br />... Keep a Nuke out for those 'Close' Last fights.<br /><br />At first you'll be wary to Mem &amp; use all these spells with your 'scary' Pet wanting to break charm and Kick your head off, but you'll very quickly become more comfortable and see the value in doing it this way. Much faster, much more efficient.<br /><br />By the way, I do everything from my Mount. Big Black Drum. Only get off your mount if you get stunned.<br /><br />Good luck, have fun, with the new Pet Exp rules I'm getting roughly 1% Exp Per '2' kills at Level 68. Or 5.0 % AA exp per kill.<br /><br /><br /><br />Edit: Oh I'm sorry, I forgot something very important.<br /><br />Self-Rune Your self and Tank...<br />Yes, I'm serious.<br /><br />Ethereal Rune, Stand opposite of your pet in front of Mob, &amp; take a few ( slowed ) rounds of hits. Re-Rune &amp; repeat, &amp; see how far you get...<br /><br />Double purpose, Prevents your pet taking damage.<br />&amp; more importantly, Turns the mob so your pet is hitting him from behind, where he will do ALOT more damage and kill the mob much faster, making your 'rounds' go much quicker.<br /><br />Sounds risky, but I can remember going through all the mobs in the Hero shrine this way with one pet and almost never dieing. Just have your Heal Pots &amp; AA Rune ready for the breaks, which yes can be painful, but death, as I said, was rare ( Once per level? )<br /><br />Yeah it uses more Mana, but If I'm NOT doing this, I never go below 90% mana through the entire round of pops, So... Why NOT do this? You'll find you can do the entire Hero shrine ( 17 mobs ) very fast, &amp; have time to med before repops, &amp;/Or move on to wanderers on the path outside, if you have the stomach for it.<br /><br />Dally<br /><br /><br /><br />Good luck.</div>

			

		</div>

		
