		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p140068">Re: HoH Solo Charming Questions</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Ishana</strong> &raquo; Mon Aug 11, 2008 11:12 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">That sounds like the normal growing pains we all had to deal with as our charming skill gradually increased.  As you see the risks that you might have to deal with, you will come up with pro-active solutions to eliminate or reduce those risks.  The first things that come to mind with HoH are, did you try to keep the mob rooted and did you use max range to your advantage?  Yes, our nukes break root easily, but if charm breaks while the mob is rooted then you are only dealing with recharming your pet instead of dealing with two mobs running after you.  If you are fighting mobs that are immune to root, I would suggest finding other mobs.  I believe HoH has changed some since I charm solo'd there last, but my favorite spots had plenty of room to move.  Enough space that I could recharm my pet on a break while it is running back to me at normal speed without moving from my near max range spot.</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile140068">
			<dt>
