			<h3 ><a href="#p140069">Re: HoH Solo Charming Questions</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Veravius</strong> &raquo; Mon Aug 11, 2008 4:46 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Ishana wrote:</cite>That sounds like the normal growing pains we all had to deal with as our charming skill gradually increased.  As you see the risks that you might have to deal with, you will come up with pro-active solutions to eliminate or reduce those risks.  The first things that come to mind with HoH are, did you try to keep the mob rooted and did you use max range to your advantage?  Yes, our nukes break root easily, but if charm breaks while the mob is rooted then you are only dealing with recharming your pet instead of dealing with two mobs running after you.  If you are fighting mobs that are immune to root, I would suggest finding other mobs.  I believe HoH has changed some since I charm solo'd there last, but my favorite spots had plenty of room to move.  Enough space that I could recharm my pet on a break while it is running back to me at normal speed without moving from my near max range spot.</div></blockquote><br /><br />Yea, after making that post last night I kind of figured out a lot of that stuff, and continued to charm for the next hour and a half to two hours with no deaths.  Finished up the third level of Total Domination and bought another level of Planar Power.<br /><br />There is one type of mob there that is immune to root, but that mob is the Valorian Sentry who doesn't spawn very often.  I got Spirit of Eagle and used the extra speed to my advantage, kiting the mobs if I needed to, and I always tried to keep the mob I was fighting rooted.  It seems like it really does take a couple of deaths before everything clicks and then you can get pretty good at it.<br /><br />Also, one other question.  I heard that with Total Domination at level 6 your charms never break early and they always last for the full duration, is this true?</div>

			

		</div>

		
