			<h3 ><a href="#p145826">Re: HoH Solo Charming Questions</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>AbyssalMage</strong> &raquo; Mon Mar 15, 2010 3:44 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Just wanted to update what I've been doing in HoH incase anyone around 65 is wondering where to go.<br />With the introduction of Merc's and the fact I have a slow connection (I.E. high lag) I can't charm the normal way.<br /><br />I head to South Temple Basement, the one with the &quot;friendly&quot; extra NPC where most people solo at. I use a J1 Tank Merc to keep the charm breaks off me and help tank the NPC's.<br /><br />Pretty standard Charm and kill really.<br /><br />AoE stun<br />Nuke<br />NDT (So merc and tank can get a 35 pt. life tap haha and I know who I charmed)<br />Mez<br />Rune<br />Tash<br />Charm<br />Slow<br />DS (Feedback)<br /><br />Occasionally I will use Pacify and sometimes I don't. I can actually kill 14 NPC's (+the NPC who respawns on the 7 minuted timer) with plenty of downtime and its 10% AA a kill. Best I have found for a laggy connection. Ive switched to nukes thanks to all the mana we have with gear inflation and the investment in Crit AA's. I also use the Ceremic Ring clicky for pulling (our level 1 or 5 DoT) to keep initial agro low but not always. Nothing special with what I do, just pull to the center of carpet until camp is broken and the suites of armour are pains in my butt but after camp is broken nothing really special about them either (can't be mez/rooted btw so thats why they are a pain for anyone new)</div>

			

		</div>

		
